Malware attack:
Trojan, adware, spyware
Corrupts your system with malicious viruses embedded within attachments you click on

Phishing attack:
Hacker sends fraudulent emails from what seems to be a legitimate source
Done to install malware or steal sensitive data


Man-in-the-middle attack:
Hacker gains access to info between your device and the websiteâ€™s server
Hacker takes over your IP address, secretly intercepting that communication line
Happens through unsecured wifi networks and malware

Password attack:
Your password gets cracked by using common passwords or using all possible alphabetical combinations

Cybersecurity practices to prevent these four methods:
Installing a firewall:
Virtual wall between your computer and the internet
Firewalls filter ingoing and outgoing traffic from your device

Honeypots:
Used to attract attackers
Made to look vulnerable to deceive attackers

Unique alpha-numeric passwords
Antivirus software
Avoiding mail from unknown senders
Cyberattacks can also happen to public & private organizations, which are more deadly

Attacks that companies are subjective to:
Advanced Persistent Threat (APT):
Hacker gains access to networks for prolonged period to continuously get confidential info

Denial of Service:
 Networks flooded with traffic, leaving actual service requests unattended

Distributed Denial of Service:
Multiple systems launch the attack

SQL injection attack
Hacker manipulates standard sql query in database driven website

Job roles in cybersecurity field:
Ethical hacker- identify network vulnerabilities to solve them
Security architect - design robust security structures
Chief Information Security Officer - entrusted with overall safety of information in an organization
